data.description: Fisherman's delight. Waterfront view of the Dworshak Reservoir and Canyon Creek boat dock & campground entrance. This year-round access home features a 25-foot ceiling with a full window view of the Dworshak and Tie Creek. It is a 2,700 sq ft, 2 bed/2 bath home build in 1995 with a 2-car garage. The recently landscaped 12.5 acre property includes a rock retention wall and a wood-sided shop/garage. The water is supplied through a 1,000 gal cistern (well production - 5gpm to be verified by the Buyer). Propane fireplace is not connected, but can be to keep the home toasty warm. Wildlife is plentiful like lawn ornaments; deer, elk, turkey. Hunters don't need to leave home.
